  <Description>Not Pork-n-Beans with BBQ sauce, but real baked beans.</Description>
  <Prerequisites>
    <Prerequisite>Put beans in a colander, rinse under cold water, discard dirt, small stones, discolored beans -anything that ain't a bean. Put beans in a large stock pot with 6 cups cold water and let soak over night.</Prerequisite>
    <Prerequisite>The next day, preheat oven to 275Â°F.</Prerequisite>
    <Prerequisite>Chop bacon into 1/4 slices, fry until browned and mostly crisp. Drain fat.</Prerequisite>
  </Prerequisites>
